		VIM

There are three modes in VIM: Normal, Insert and Visual

install vim:	sudo apt-install vim

creating a file and entering vim: vim filename.txt

i	:	enters into INSERT mode and the text is prepended at the cursor
<ESC>	:	returns to normal mode
a	:	enters into INSERT mode and the text appended at the cursor
h	:	moves cursor left
j	:	moves cursor down
k	:	moves cursor up
l	:	moves cursor right

(count)h/j/k/l	:	moves the cursor count number of times in specified direction e.g 3k ---moves up 3 lines

dd	:	deletes the line in which cursor is
dw	:	deletes next word
d$	:	deletes the line left after cursor
$	:	moves cursor to the end of the line
0	:	moves cursor to the end of the line
w	:	moves to next word's first char
b	:	moves to previous word's first char
e	:	moves to next word's last char
f(char)	:	searches for the first appearance of mentioned character in forward dir
F(char)	:	searches for the first appearance of mentioned character in backward dir
<CTR>G	:	Lists the file info
o	:	adds a new line
x	:	deletes the character under cursor
:q!	:	quit and throw the things away
:wq!	:	write and quit
:w!	:	write only
(count)G:	puts us on line number count
:set number:	shows the line numbering
:set nonumber:	hides the line numbering
u	:	undo
<CTR>r	:	redo
cw	:	deletes next word upto space and puts us in INSERT mode
cc	:	deletes entire line and enters in INSERT mode

